WEBVTT

00:04.047 --> 00:04.265
.

00:04.308 --> 00:06.615
- Oh, that sounds cool.
I tell you what,

00:06.658 --> 00:07.529
recess was always
my favorite part of school.

00:07.572 --> 00:09.139
- Yup.
- What else?

00:09.183 --> 00:11.489
- Well, we learned that
Jupiter's the biggest planet

00:11.533 --> 00:13.491
and Saturn has a bunch
of rings around it.

00:13.535 --> 00:15.493
- Hmm.
- And my new friend, Teddy,

00:15.537 --> 00:18.279
gave me this new sticker
today during recess.

00:18.322 --> 00:19.584
A cute little strawberry.

00:19.628 --> 00:21.456
- Oh, it is
a cute little strawberry.

00:21.499 --> 00:24.154
My gosh, what
an action-packed day you had.

00:24.198 --> 00:25.503
Is that everything?
- Mm-hmm.

00:25.547 --> 00:26.548
- You ready to hit it?
- Yup.

00:26.591 --> 00:27.723
Let's go.

00:27.766 --> 00:29.594
I got a question for you, Mack.

00:29.638 --> 00:31.335
Pluto, is it still a planet

00:31.379 --> 00:33.120
or have they officially
left it behind?

00:33.163 --> 00:34.425
- Well...
- Well, what?

00:34.469 --> 00:36.253
- Well, we--
- Excuse me, excuse me?

00:36.297 --> 00:38.690
I'm sorry, I have to stop you.
Who are you?

00:38.734 --> 00:40.823
- I'm sorry?
- Who are you?

00:40.866 --> 00:44.348
- Oh, my name's Adam Ruzek.
- And you're Makayla's...

00:44.392 --> 00:45.480
- Oh, I'm--

00:45.523 --> 00:46.785
- You're not her father,
I take it?

00:46.829 --> 00:48.700
- No, ma'am.
- Sorry, her guardian, I mean.

00:48.744 --> 00:50.224
- No, not officially.
I'm just here--

00:50.267 --> 00:53.096
- He's my friend.
- You're darn right.

00:53.140 --> 00:56.273
I'm her friend.
Kim Burgess is her guardian.

00:56.317 --> 00:57.535
I'm just here
to pick Makayla up for--

00:57.579 --> 00:59.581
- She didn't authorize you
for pick up.

00:59.624 --> 01:01.191
- Oh, okay, gotcha.
I'm sorry.

01:01.235 --> 01:02.714
I didn't know that was a thing.

01:02.758 --> 01:04.151
- Makayla, honey, can you
step over here with me please?

01:04.194 --> 01:05.500
- No, she's fine
with me, ma'am.

01:05.543 --> 01:06.631
I just--I'm gonna call Kim.

01:06.675 --> 01:08.198
We're gonna get this
straightened out.

01:08.242 --> 01:10.548
- I'm still gonna need her
to step over here with me, sir.

01:10.592 --> 01:12.768
Come on, honey.

01:12.811 --> 01:15.553
[apprehensive music]

01:15.597 --> 01:17.120
- It's all right, Mack.
Go on.

01:17.164 --> 01:18.730
- All right.
Come on. This way.

01:21.820 --> 01:23.518
- I'm sure you understand.
We can't let an unauthorized--

01:23.561 --> 01:25.346
- I understand.
- For all she could've known--

01:25.389 --> 01:26.608
- Sir, you keep
explaining yourself.

01:26.651 --> 01:28.566
I get it, it's just,
I showed you my badge

01:28.610 --> 01:31.134
and yet, you still got Makayla
sitting in there by herself

01:31.178 --> 01:33.832
watching all this go down.
- I'm here.

01:35.530 --> 01:36.922
Adam is authorized
to pick up Makayla.

01:36.966 --> 01:39.751
I just forgot to put his name
on the paperwork.

01:39.795 --> 01:41.362
Just a mistake.
- These things happen.

01:41.405 --> 01:42.711
- Yeah.

01:42.754 --> 01:44.321
- We'll just need you
to resubmit the paperwork.

01:44.365 --> 01:46.323
- Am I good to go get Mack now?
- Yes.

01:47.933 --> 01:49.587
All right, let's go.
- Let's do it.

01:49.631 --> 01:50.632
- Okay.

01:52.982 --> 01:54.766
- I completely forgot
when I asked you

01:54.810 --> 01:56.333
to pick her up this morning.
I'm so sorry.

01:56.377 --> 01:57.552
- It's fine.

01:57.595 --> 01:59.771
You did submit it
last month though, right?

01:59.815 --> 02:01.860
- What, her authorization form?
- Yeah, it was last month.

02:01.904 --> 02:03.601
I thought you put
me down automatically.

02:03.645 --> 02:05.647
- Makayla, please slow down
and wait for us.

02:05.690 --> 02:08.302
I think I just figured
you wouldn't be picking her up.

02:08.345 --> 02:10.608
I mean, I can usually make it.
[phone buzzes]

02:10.652 --> 02:12.262
What?

02:12.306 --> 02:14.351
- Voight's got a potential
missing tender age.

02:14.395 --> 02:15.918
- [sighs]
You take it.

02:15.961 --> 02:17.267
I'll drop Makayla off.
- Copy.

02:17.311 --> 02:19.704
- Let's go.
- Yeah.

02:19.748 --> 02:21.184
- I told them this already.

02:21.228 --> 02:23.317
I do a Zoom meeting every day
at that time.

02:23.360 --> 02:26.537
- Okay, so when was the last
time you saw your daughter?

02:26.581 --> 02:29.888
- I--what are they doing?

02:29.932 --> 02:32.717
- Just taking a look around
the neighborhood, Simone.

02:32.761 --> 02:34.980
Can you tell me when the
last time you saw Brianna was?

02:35.024 --> 02:36.634
- I don't know.
- Okay.

02:36.678 --> 02:38.506
- Oh God.

02:40.334 --> 02:42.814
I don't know.

02:42.858 --> 02:45.339
She always likes to play
in the backyard after school.

02:45.382 --> 02:47.471
I check on her
every ten minutes.

02:47.515 --> 02:49.343
- I understand.

02:49.386 --> 02:52.302
All right, do you have
a recent picture of Brianna?

02:52.346 --> 02:53.521
- Yeah.

02:53.564 --> 02:59.222
♪

02:59.266 --> 03:00.919
- Oh, that's a cute kid.
She about seven?

03:00.963 --> 03:02.486
- Mm-hmm.
- That's a good age.

03:02.530 --> 03:04.009
- Yeah, it sure is.

03:04.053 --> 03:07.230
All right, listen, I just
want you to stay right here.

03:07.274 --> 03:08.797
Okay?
Keep your phone nearby

03:08.840 --> 03:10.668
in case someone calls.
She's gonna sit with you.

03:10.712 --> 03:12.757
We're just gonna take
another look around the yard.

03:12.801 --> 03:13.802
All right?
- Okay.

03:13.845 --> 03:14.890
- All right.

03:20.939 --> 03:23.899
- So what are we
really looking at?

03:23.942 --> 03:25.640
- Patrol responded.

03:25.683 --> 03:28.904
Simone was running through
the neighborhood, panicked.

03:28.947 --> 03:32.342
And Brianna disappeared
from the backyard.

03:32.386 --> 03:34.344
They found evidence of blood.

03:35.606 --> 03:37.347
Was open when they got here.

03:39.784 --> 03:43.266
The blood they found.
- All right.

03:43.310 --> 03:45.790
Well, I mean, it's possible
she got hurt, wandered off.

03:45.834 --> 03:48.445
Makayla's always getting cuts,
scrapes, bleeding.

03:54.016 --> 03:56.366
Boss.

03:56.410 --> 03:59.369
[suspenseful music]

03:59.413 --> 04:06.420
♪

04:21.696 --> 04:23.698
- All calls lodged?

04:23.741 --> 04:25.308
- Yes, sir.
Missing tender age,

04:25.352 --> 04:26.744
we already threw out
a BOLO and an Amber Alert.

04:26.788 --> 04:28.355
- And a dedicated
tip-line at 21.

04:28.398 --> 04:29.486
- Mobile crime lab's
on its way,

04:29.530 --> 04:30.966
Forensics is moving in,

04:31.009 --> 04:32.576
and CPIC is pulling all
the POD footage in the area.

04:32.620 --> 04:34.448
- And we need all door cams,
NEST cameras,

04:34.491 --> 04:36.885
anything we can get
and all in-service calls.

04:36.928 --> 04:38.974
Hailey, talk to the mom.
We need more info.

04:39.017 --> 04:40.018
- Okay.

04:42.847 --> 04:45.023
- You guys got married.
- Yeah, we did.

04:46.590 --> 04:48.592
- What the hell?
Congratulations.

04:48.636 --> 04:51.465
- Guys, we have work to do.

04:51.508 --> 04:52.292
- Sarge.

04:54.642 --> 04:56.034
I got a neighbor
who heard something.

04:56.078 --> 04:57.906
Second house there,
a woman heard what she thought

04:57.949 --> 05:00.474
was screaming from the alley.
A car racing away.

05:00.517 --> 05:02.040
She went to look out
her back window,

05:02.084 --> 05:03.912
didn't see a thing.

05:03.955 --> 05:05.957
It's the real deal.

05:06.001 --> 05:07.785
Feels like
a stranger abduction.

05:11.615 --> 05:14.662
- Why are you in here?
I told you Brianna was outside.

05:14.705 --> 05:16.141
- Mrs. Hall,
I know this is difficult,

05:16.185 --> 05:17.665
but I need you to stay with me.

05:17.708 --> 05:19.667
Do you know of anyone that
would want to take Brianna?

05:19.710 --> 05:20.711
- Take her?

05:22.191 --> 05:24.498
Of course not.
- Okay.

05:24.541 --> 05:25.890
Where's your husband?

05:25.934 --> 05:27.892
- He's on his way home.

05:27.936 --> 05:30.460
He was away at Springfield.
He's driving back now.

05:30.504 --> 05:33.681
- What's in Springfield?
- A client.

05:33.724 --> 05:35.160
I don't know which.

05:35.204 --> 05:38.425
- Ma'am, does Brianna use
a tablet or a laptop?

05:38.468 --> 05:39.774
- Yes, it's in her room,

05:39.817 --> 05:41.515
but she's only allowed
to use it when I'm around.

05:41.558 --> 05:44.648
- Her room is...
- Upstairs, last door.

05:44.692 --> 05:46.694
- May I?
- Yeah, sure.

05:50.524 --> 05:51.655
- Mrs. Hall,
we're gonna do everything

05:51.699 --> 05:55.093
we can to find her, okay?
I promise.

06:04.538 --> 06:07.105
- Hey.
- Hey.

06:07.149 --> 06:09.978
Makayla with the sitter?
- Yeah, she's all set.

06:10.021 --> 06:12.676
- I haven't checked
those drawers yet.

06:12.720 --> 06:14.504
Parents worst nightmare
here, huh?

06:14.548 --> 06:16.027
- Yeah.

06:17.986 --> 06:19.944
Girl's really
into martial arts.

06:19.988 --> 06:21.946
- You get the paperwork
for Makayla all settled?

06:21.990 --> 06:23.774
- Yeah, it's all sorted.
I sent it right in.

06:23.818 --> 06:26.037
- And soccer, dance,

06:26.081 --> 06:28.475
I'm good to pick her up
from those, right?

06:28.518 --> 06:31.521
[phone buzzing]
- Um, I can call them, sure.

06:31.565 --> 06:33.915
I just need to add you on.

06:33.958 --> 06:35.743
Door cam footage is up.

06:40.617 --> 06:43.011
- Okay,
this is 2:17 p.m. today.

06:44.578 --> 06:46.580
Door cam position
is the mom's backyard.

06:46.623 --> 06:48.843
You see that obstructed view
of the alley right there.

06:51.498 --> 06:53.587
- Hey, wait. Go back.
- Okay.

06:55.545 --> 06:57.852
- There.

06:57.895 --> 07:00.724
What she looking at?
We got any other cameras?

07:00.768 --> 07:02.683
- No, I got nothing yet.

07:02.726 --> 07:05.120
I mean, if you ask me,
she's looking at somebody.

07:05.163 --> 07:07.035
Somebody was stopped
right there in that alley.

07:07.078 --> 07:08.210
- Hey, we got
a track and trace set up

07:08.253 --> 07:09.603
on both the Hall's phones,

07:09.646 --> 07:11.996
so if a kidnapper contacts them
we're gonna know.

07:12.040 --> 07:14.216
Also, there's five registered
sex offenders

07:14.259 --> 07:15.739
within a two-mile radius.

07:18.263 --> 07:19.569
- Okay.

07:19.613 --> 07:21.571
We keep our minds wide.

07:21.615 --> 07:23.094
And every one
of those sex offenders

07:23.138 --> 07:25.053
has a cleared alibi
or we bring them in.

07:25.096 --> 07:27.011
And we do a full rundown
on this family.

07:27.055 --> 07:28.535
And we
knock and talk ourselves,

07:28.578 --> 07:29.840
you understand?
- Copy that.

07:29.884 --> 07:32.103
- Jay and Kev, you hit
the sex offender list.

07:32.147 --> 07:33.714
The rest of you
start talking to neighbors.

07:33.757 --> 07:35.150
All right, let's go.

07:35.193 --> 07:38.849
[suspenseful music]

07:38.893 --> 07:41.983
♪

07:42.026 --> 07:44.028
- Hey there, Chicago PD.

07:44.072 --> 07:46.509
I'm Detective Halstead.
This is Officer Atwater.

07:46.553 --> 07:48.772
- You all just come over
whenever you want.

07:48.816 --> 07:50.948
- Well, you lose certain
freedoms when you prey on kids.

07:50.992 --> 07:54.691
What were you doing between
1:00 and 3:00 p.m. today?

07:54.735 --> 07:56.040
- I got a root canal.

07:56.084 --> 07:57.520
- We need that dentist's info.

07:59.827 --> 08:01.306
- Have you seen
that little girl?

08:01.350 --> 08:03.265
- Oh, I've seen her
around the block, yes.

08:03.308 --> 08:05.659
But I was at the studio.

08:05.702 --> 08:07.269
I taught three classes
back-to-back

08:07.312 --> 08:09.227
and picked up my grandkids.

08:09.271 --> 08:10.794
- Do you have
any security cameras?

08:10.838 --> 08:13.318
- Oh, no. I'm so sorry.

08:13.362 --> 08:15.886
I guess I should.
- But I don't.

08:15.930 --> 08:17.018
And I'm sorry,

08:17.061 --> 08:18.323
I can't say
that I recognize her.

08:18.367 --> 08:20.151
There's a lot of kids
in this neighborhood,

08:20.195 --> 08:22.589
it's supposed to be safe.

08:22.632 --> 08:24.025
I wish I could help you more.

08:24.068 --> 08:25.853
- Were you here today?

08:25.896 --> 08:28.812
- Earlier, yes, but then
I went to the park to paint.

08:28.856 --> 08:31.032
- Look, I know exactly
why you're here

08:31.075 --> 08:32.816
because my stepfather--
- Is Richard Brodsky.

08:32.860 --> 08:34.557
- Yeah, freaking pervert,
I know.

08:34.601 --> 08:37.038
I wouldn't let
my own kids near him,

08:37.081 --> 08:38.561
but he died of a stroke
a week ago.

08:38.605 --> 08:39.954
I'm just packing up.

08:39.997 --> 08:42.173
I'm sorry,
I don't know who that girl is.

08:42.217 --> 08:43.784
- She looks like
the Halls girl.

08:43.827 --> 08:45.568
Is that right?
- Yes, sir.

08:45.612 --> 08:47.657
- Yeah, no,
she rides her bike around here.

08:47.701 --> 08:49.877
My God, that poor family.

08:49.920 --> 08:53.924
They care about
that girl so much.

08:53.968 --> 08:57.188
I mean, most of the time
they're just--

08:57.232 --> 08:59.016
- Most of the time what?

08:59.060 --> 09:00.801
- [groans]
I shouldn't.

09:00.844 --> 09:02.193
It's fully out of line.

09:02.237 --> 09:03.804
- It's certainly not
out of line, sir.

09:03.847 --> 09:04.935
A child's missing.

09:04.979 --> 09:06.720
What do you mean
"most of the time?"

09:08.286 --> 09:12.203
- Most of the time,
they're arguing about her.

09:12.247 --> 09:14.728
What's best for her.

09:14.771 --> 09:18.688
They live a few houses down.
I--I've heard them.

09:18.732 --> 09:22.257
The dad gets pretty fired up.

09:22.300 --> 09:25.303
- Okay.
- Too much love, right?

09:27.349 --> 09:29.264
- All right, well,
thank you for your time, sir.

09:29.307 --> 09:30.831
Thank you.
- Thank you, officer.

09:30.874 --> 09:32.615
- I need to see my wife.

09:32.659 --> 09:35.226
My girl is gone and I--
- Sir, sir, sir.

09:35.270 --> 09:38.099
I understand, but you gotta
answer our questions first.

09:38.142 --> 09:40.754
Okay? So where were you today?

09:40.797 --> 09:43.931
- I was at a client's.
My wife told you.

09:43.974 --> 09:45.106
I'm in software development.

09:45.149 --> 09:46.890
- Can anyone corroborate that?
- Yes.

09:46.934 --> 09:49.937
Of course, the whole team.
- Okay.

09:49.980 --> 09:52.113
So how's your marriage?
- What?

09:52.156 --> 09:53.723
- Do you fight, have arguments,

09:53.767 --> 09:55.899
disagreements about Brianna?
- What the hell is this?

09:55.943 --> 09:57.292
- This is me trying
to find your daughter.

09:57.335 --> 09:58.902
- And my marriage
has to do with that?

09:58.946 --> 10:00.861
- Mr. Hall, we understand
that this is uncomfortable.

10:00.904 --> 10:02.689
- No, you don't.

10:06.693 --> 10:10.261
Do I fight with my wife?
Yes, we fight.

10:10.305 --> 10:13.917
We argue. You want to know why?

10:13.961 --> 10:17.747
She thinks I'm overprotective--
overprotective--

10:17.791 --> 10:21.272
because I don't like
their afternoon routine.

10:21.316 --> 10:23.100
You think she's still
gonna see it that way

10:23.144 --> 10:24.711
after she left
my daughter alone

10:24.754 --> 10:27.627
in the goddamn backyard
so someone could...

10:32.109 --> 10:34.677
[sighs]
I didn't hurt my kid.

10:34.721 --> 10:35.852
[knock at door]

10:37.375 --> 10:39.073
- Sarge.

10:44.992 --> 10:47.385
Simone and Niles' alibis
are airtight,

10:47.429 --> 10:49.126
but we found one
that didn't check out.

10:49.170 --> 10:51.302
There's a Charles Kalzenski
who lives two blocks down.

10:51.346 --> 10:52.695
We talked to him.
- Right.

10:52.739 --> 10:54.349
- And he volunteered
he was at the park painting

10:54.392 --> 10:56.220
when Brianna disappeared.
- He wasn't?

10:56.264 --> 10:57.831
- No, we caught him
on a neighbor's door cam

10:57.874 --> 10:59.397
going the opposite direction
of the park

10:59.441 --> 11:01.835
towards the alley Brianna
disappeared from at 2:15,

11:01.878 --> 11:05.229
which is minutes
before she disappeared.

11:05.273 --> 11:07.710
And it gets a lot worse.

11:07.754 --> 11:10.452
There's a Charles Kalzenski
in the sex offender database.

11:10.495 --> 11:11.932
It's the same guy, Sarge.

11:11.975 --> 11:13.673
He just didn't update
his address when he moved.

11:15.457 --> 11:17.764
And he's a tender age
pedophile.

11:17.807 --> 11:19.374
- Judge gave the green light
on the exigent.

11:19.417 --> 11:21.855
- Go.

11:21.898 --> 11:23.117
- Chicago PD!

11:23.160 --> 11:26.207
[tense music]

11:26.250 --> 11:27.861
- Burge, doors.
- I got it.

11:33.083 --> 11:34.084
Move.

11:36.043 --> 11:38.349
- Stairs, anything?

11:38.393 --> 11:39.699
Go.

11:42.397 --> 11:44.921
Door.
- Moving.

11:44.965 --> 11:46.749
Going down.

11:46.793 --> 11:53.800
♪

11:57.586 --> 11:59.457
- Upstairs, clear.

11:59.501 --> 12:02.199
- Downstairs, clear.

12:02.243 --> 12:04.549
- All clear, house is empty.

12:04.593 --> 12:11.731
♪

12:30.488 --> 12:30.706
.

12:30.750 --> 12:32.708
- Okay, tell me
we got something.

12:32.752 --> 12:34.057
- We got CPIC
running traffic cams.

12:34.101 --> 12:35.450
- Forensics scrubbed the house.

12:35.493 --> 12:36.799
There's nothing linking
Brianna to the residence.

12:36.843 --> 12:38.670
We got a BOLO out
on Charlie and his vehicle.

12:38.714 --> 12:40.672
No hits yet.
It looks like he's on the lam.

12:40.716 --> 12:42.718
- He cleaned out some clothes.
Emptied out his fridge.

12:42.762 --> 12:44.154
We have to assume
that he still has Brianna

12:44.198 --> 12:45.590
and is headed somewhere.

12:45.634 --> 12:47.244
- Okay, so what do we
know about him?

12:47.288 --> 12:48.985
- He was arrested eight years
ago for inappropriate touching

12:49.029 --> 12:50.813
while he was working
as a school photographer.

12:50.857 --> 12:53.511
- All reported victims are
seven- to eight-year-old girls,

12:53.555 --> 12:55.557
which is an exact age match
to Brianna.

12:55.600 --> 12:57.689
- Yeah, he got a plea deal
and he did zero jail time.

12:57.733 --> 12:59.561
- All right, what do we
have on timing?

12:59.604 --> 13:01.693
- All right, well,
Charlie's car moves

13:01.737 --> 13:02.999
towards the alley
where Brianna disappeared.

13:03.043 --> 13:05.132
2:15, we lose eyes.

13:05.175 --> 13:07.003
It's plenty of time for him
to turn to that alley,

13:07.047 --> 13:09.440
lure Brianna,
she's gone by 2:17.

13:09.484 --> 13:11.138
- Any luck tracking him on GPS?

13:11.181 --> 13:12.617
- We can't,
he doesn't own a phone.

13:12.661 --> 13:14.010
He's not allowed
to use the internet.

13:14.054 --> 13:15.490
Part of his plea deal.

13:15.533 --> 13:17.144
- We can't track a criminal
because of a court order.

13:17.187 --> 13:18.667
Ain't that some irony?
[phone buzzes]

13:18.710 --> 13:20.408
- Brianna's parents are
headed in now with patrol.

13:20.451 --> 13:22.453
They'll confirm if Charlie
had previous contact.

13:22.497 --> 13:24.455
- Hey, got a hit on the BOLO.

13:24.499 --> 13:25.892
All right, tech found
Charlie's car.

13:25.935 --> 13:27.023
They're sitting on it
right now in Humboldt.

13:27.067 --> 13:29.721
- Go, you and Kev.

13:29.765 --> 13:33.029
[suspenseful music]

13:33.073 --> 13:34.770
- Sedan's been sitting there
20 minutes now.

13:34.814 --> 13:36.119
It matches your BOLO.
- Okay.

13:36.163 --> 13:37.860
You didn't approach, did you?
- No, we didn't.

13:37.904 --> 13:39.470
We thought we shouldn't.
- Okay.

13:39.514 --> 13:40.689
Hold it down, all right?
Thanks.

13:43.083 --> 13:45.128
All right, here's the fun part.

13:45.172 --> 13:46.695
- Good DI.

13:46.738 --> 13:53.745
♪

14:03.016 --> 14:04.452
[sighs]

14:06.933 --> 14:08.108
No body.

14:12.634 --> 14:13.722
Kev.

14:15.898 --> 14:17.030
- Call it in.

14:21.599 --> 14:22.905
- Yeah, send over
whatever you got.

14:22.949 --> 14:24.472
- Got another camera
coming now,

14:24.515 --> 14:26.822
facing the north east corner
of 48th and State.

14:26.866 --> 14:28.868
- Okay, copy.
- All right, where are we?

14:28.911 --> 14:31.218
- All right,
so we've got Charlie here

14:31.261 --> 14:33.785
parking his car on 48th Street
where we found it.

14:33.829 --> 14:35.831
There's an obstructed view
of him exiting the vehicle

14:35.875 --> 14:37.659
carrying a bag.
- But no Brianna.

14:37.702 --> 14:39.313
- No, he's alone.

14:39.356 --> 14:41.924
Next time we catch him is here
on 48th Street on the corner.

14:41.968 --> 14:43.143
Then a convenience store camera

14:43.186 --> 14:44.927
picks him up
three minutes after that.

14:44.971 --> 14:46.929
And then a minute after that,
we assume he keeps walking

14:46.973 --> 14:49.105
in that direction,
but we have a blind spot.

14:49.149 --> 14:51.499
- Parents confirmed
they know Charlie.

14:51.542 --> 14:52.979
Simone said he likes
to walk the neighborhood

14:53.022 --> 14:54.763
and say "hi" to Brianna.

14:54.806 --> 14:56.504
They also think
the sweatshirt might be hers,

14:56.547 --> 14:59.115
but they can't confirm.
They're in shock, unreliable.

14:59.159 --> 15:00.290
- I think we got him.

15:00.334 --> 15:02.031
Last camera picked up
the blind spot.

15:04.338 --> 15:06.253
- Can we get that address?
- Yup.

15:06.296 --> 15:08.124
That's 4280 Miller.

15:08.168 --> 15:10.039
It's Legacy Offsite
Document Storage

15:10.083 --> 15:13.216
and--hold on a sec--

15:13.260 --> 15:15.871
Charlie worked there
between 2015 and 2019.

15:15.915 --> 15:17.177
- Go.

15:17.220 --> 15:20.180
[tense music]

15:20.223 --> 15:27.230
♪

15:45.857 --> 15:48.556
- East side, lots of boxes.
That's it.

15:48.599 --> 15:55.606
♪

16:01.917 --> 16:03.788
- I got eyes on his bag
and some bedding.

16:03.832 --> 16:04.833
It looks like
he was camping here.

16:04.876 --> 16:06.704
- Copy.

16:06.748 --> 16:07.792
- All right,
I'm right here with you.

16:07.836 --> 16:09.055
Let's go.

16:17.977 --> 16:20.849
- All right, I got right.

16:25.897 --> 16:27.290
- There's a break room
up here.

16:27.334 --> 16:29.379
No sign of anyone.

16:29.423 --> 16:30.728
- Yeah, copy.

16:30.772 --> 16:35.385
♪

16:35.429 --> 16:37.213
Moving toward the back
of the building.

16:37.257 --> 16:38.736
- I'm right behind you.

16:38.780 --> 16:39.999
- Chicago PD, stop!

16:45.961 --> 16:47.180
- I got him.

16:47.223 --> 16:49.225
Come on, get up.

16:49.269 --> 16:51.053
Hands up.
- Second floor is clear.

16:51.097 --> 16:53.708
No sign of Brianna.
- East side clear.

16:53.751 --> 16:55.231
- Copy that.
Offender's in custody.

16:57.277 --> 16:59.061
Hello, Charlie.

16:59.105 --> 17:00.628
So where is she?

17:03.239 --> 17:04.762
Huh?

17:09.724 --> 17:09.898
.

17:09.941 --> 17:11.552
- Where is she?

17:11.595 --> 17:13.293
- I told you.
I told you everything--

17:13.336 --> 17:14.816
- No, we're not going
to keep doing this.

17:14.859 --> 17:16.818
We're not gonna keep going
around in circles, Charlie.

17:16.861 --> 17:19.821
- I didn't take her.

17:19.864 --> 17:22.215
- Again,
we have a child's sweatshirt

17:22.258 --> 17:23.346
in the trunk of your car.

17:23.390 --> 17:24.695
We have you on video driving

17:24.739 --> 17:26.393
towards the alley
where Brianna disappeared.

17:27.959 --> 17:31.572
- I only drove that way because
I can't drive by a school.

17:31.615 --> 17:32.834
The plea deal--

17:32.877 --> 17:34.357
- Right and the fact
that you ran.

17:34.401 --> 17:36.490
- I knew what you would think.

17:36.533 --> 17:37.882
Seriously, I knew what
this would look like.

17:37.926 --> 17:39.319
- That's what
you're sticking with, huh?

17:39.362 --> 17:41.669
- I--I knew that
I would be a suspect.

17:41.712 --> 17:43.497
[chuckles]

17:43.540 --> 17:47.892
- Charlie, you have a painting
of her in your house.

17:47.936 --> 17:49.459
- No.

17:49.503 --> 17:52.636
No, no, that is only because
I can't take photos anymore.

17:52.680 --> 17:55.509
- Right, because
you molested children.

17:55.552 --> 17:56.945
- I--

18:01.776 --> 18:03.995
I would never knowingly
hurt a child.

18:04.039 --> 18:07.260
- Oh, my God. Oh, my God.

18:07.303 --> 18:08.826
- I love children.

18:11.742 --> 18:12.961
Do you have a child?

18:16.399 --> 18:18.271
- We are not talking about me.

18:18.314 --> 18:21.274
[tense music]

18:21.317 --> 18:24.364
♪

18:24.407 --> 18:26.627
- I didn't take her.

18:26.670 --> 18:28.498
Someone else must've taken her.

18:28.542 --> 18:30.718
I saw other people out
when I was driving.

18:30.761 --> 18:34.374
I saw a woman jogging.
Someone was walking their dog.

18:34.417 --> 18:35.940
A woman driving--
- Stop.

18:35.984 --> 18:40.293
- I saw a white car.
- Stop, stop.

18:40.336 --> 18:47.300
♪

18:47.343 --> 18:48.953
Where is she?

18:51.956 --> 18:53.784
- I don't know.

19:00.051 --> 19:02.358
- You get anything yet?
- No, he's still denying it.

19:02.402 --> 19:04.708
Now he's trying
to offer new suspects.

19:04.752 --> 19:07.058
- All right, tell me
we got something else.

19:07.102 --> 19:08.408
- No, not yet.

19:08.451 --> 19:09.887
No DNA from Brianna
in that building.

19:09.931 --> 19:11.106
No DNA on his clothes.

19:11.150 --> 19:12.934
- Forensics are
still working his vehicle.

19:12.977 --> 19:15.502
- Look, he takes Brianna
at 2:17,

19:15.545 --> 19:17.895
two hours later we're
talking to him at his house.

19:17.939 --> 19:20.028
So where the hell
was he in those two hours?

19:20.071 --> 19:21.290
- We're still pulling
POD footage.

19:21.334 --> 19:22.422
We got nothing yet.

19:22.465 --> 19:23.553
- Well, he didn't
just disappear.

19:23.597 --> 19:25.033
Neither did Brianna.

19:25.076 --> 19:27.731
All right, just keep pulling
everything we can.

19:27.775 --> 19:29.646
- Boss, this guy seems
real aware

19:29.690 --> 19:30.952
of the freedoms
he no longer enjoys.

19:30.995 --> 19:32.301
- Okay.

19:32.345 --> 19:33.955
- I'd like to take
a few more away from him.

19:33.998 --> 19:36.523
- Yeah, do it.

19:36.566 --> 19:39.526
Kev, meantime,
keep an eye on him.

19:39.569 --> 19:40.788
- You want all of these?

19:40.831 --> 19:43.051
- Yeah, the more the better.
- Okay.

19:45.009 --> 19:46.402
- You all right?
- Yeah.

19:46.446 --> 19:49.797
It's just those poor parents,
I can't imagine.

19:49.840 --> 19:52.626
This case just feels
so different since Makayla.

19:53.888 --> 19:55.977
- Can I ask you something?
- Yeah, what's up?

19:56.020 --> 19:58.066
- Why wasn't I
on any of the paperwork?

19:59.676 --> 20:02.331
If it's nothing
and I'm overthinking things,

20:02.375 --> 20:03.637
you just tell me
to shut the hell up.

20:03.680 --> 20:05.029
It just felt
a little intentional.

20:05.073 --> 20:07.031
- I think we should
talk about this later, okay?

20:13.821 --> 20:15.388
- Please tell me now.

20:15.431 --> 20:19.130
♪

20:19.174 --> 20:21.611
- I think it would be better
if we had...

20:23.047 --> 20:25.615
More boundaries with Makayla.

20:25.659 --> 20:28.705
Less official, you know?
Make it easier if...

20:28.749 --> 20:31.186
- If what?

20:31.230 --> 20:32.579
- I don't know.

20:32.622 --> 20:33.710
- Yes, you do, Kim. What?

20:33.754 --> 20:35.234
- Okay, if you ever
weren't around.

20:35.277 --> 20:38.498
I think it would be easier
if you ever weren't around.

20:38.541 --> 20:40.935
I'm only being realistic.

20:40.978 --> 20:42.806
We're not dating.
You could meet someone.

20:42.850 --> 20:44.808
You could fall in love
and want your own family.

20:44.852 --> 20:46.680
You're gonna want to move out.
- And I'm just gonna leave her?

20:46.723 --> 20:48.508
- That's not what I'm saying.
- Are you guys gonna leave me?

20:48.551 --> 20:50.074
- Adam, listen to me.
- Because, Kim,

20:50.118 --> 20:52.642
everything that you just
said to me is true for you too.

20:52.686 --> 20:53.904
And from where I'm sitting,

20:53.948 --> 20:55.906
I got no right
to be in her life right now.

20:55.950 --> 20:58.431
I'm some backup plan
that sleeps on your couch.

20:58.474 --> 20:59.867
- Hey.

20:59.910 --> 21:01.042
Oh, I'm sorry, are y'all...

21:01.085 --> 21:02.739
- No, man, we're fine.

21:04.915 --> 21:06.439
We're fine.

21:06.482 --> 21:09.137
You ready to go?
- Yeah, media's got it.

21:09.180 --> 21:10.573
- Let's do it.

21:10.617 --> 21:17.624
♪

21:21.976 --> 21:24.631
So let me make something
real clear to you.

21:24.674 --> 21:28.069
I'm not leaving
until I get what I need.

21:28.112 --> 21:30.898
So I want you
to think real hard

21:30.941 --> 21:32.987
because what you say to me
in this room

21:33.030 --> 21:35.206
is gonna play a big part
in what happens to you next.

21:35.250 --> 21:36.904
Do you understand?

21:36.947 --> 21:38.732
- I already told you
so many times--

21:38.775 --> 21:39.820
- No, no, no.

21:39.863 --> 21:41.474
No, no, no.

21:41.517 --> 21:44.738
You have lied to me
so many times.

21:44.781 --> 21:46.609
We're gonna stop
lying to ourselves now.

21:48.481 --> 21:50.047
Tara Martinez.
- [groans]

21:52.789 --> 21:55.662
- Meredith Melnyk.
- Oh, God, I--

21:55.705 --> 21:58.055
- Libby Cole.

21:58.099 --> 21:59.492
These are the kids
that you hurt.

21:59.535 --> 22:01.929
- I never meant--
- You know that Libby Cole?

22:01.972 --> 22:04.932
She committed suicide
when she was 15 years old

22:04.975 --> 22:06.542
because of what you did.
- No.

22:06.586 --> 22:07.804
- You killed her, Charlie.

22:07.848 --> 22:08.936
What you did to her,
killed her.

22:08.979 --> 22:10.764
- I didn't...

22:10.807 --> 22:12.548
- Why don't you
give these a read.

22:14.637 --> 22:16.030
Read it.

22:19.816 --> 22:24.125
- Beware Charlie Kalzenski,

22:24.168 --> 22:26.780
pedophile.

22:26.823 --> 22:29.304
Person of interest
in the disappearance

22:29.348 --> 22:31.132
of seven-year-old...

22:31.175 --> 22:32.612
both: Brianna Hall.

22:32.655 --> 22:34.831
- I didn't...
- Yeah.

22:34.875 --> 22:36.964
And that's you.

22:37.007 --> 22:38.531
- I didn't...
- These are up all over

22:38.574 --> 22:40.010
your neighborhood
because someone

22:40.054 --> 22:41.838
leaked your arrest
to the press.

22:43.710 --> 22:45.233
- [sighs]

22:46.800 --> 22:48.802
- The whole neighborhood knows
exactly who you are now.

22:48.845 --> 22:50.151
- Oh, God.
- I know who you are.

22:50.194 --> 22:52.806
You know who you are.
It's over, Charlie.

22:52.849 --> 22:54.547
- [sighs]
- So come on.

22:54.590 --> 22:58.246
Just tell me the truth.
What happened to her?

22:58.289 --> 22:59.726
- I never wanted
to hurt anyone.

22:59.769 --> 23:01.423
I...
- But you did.

23:01.467 --> 23:03.904
You grabbed her from her yard
'cause you wanted to touch her.

23:03.947 --> 23:05.601
And then what happened?
- No.

23:05.645 --> 23:07.037
- She pushed you away,
you got angry,

23:07.081 --> 23:08.996
then you hurt her?
- No.

23:09.039 --> 23:10.954
- No?
- I can't tell you...

23:10.998 --> 23:13.783
- Charlie, you got to remember,
this is where we are now.

23:13.827 --> 23:15.176
Yeah?

23:15.219 --> 23:18.309
This is where we are now.

23:18.353 --> 23:19.746
Yeah?
- [mumbles]

23:19.789 --> 23:21.661
- It's out.
- Oh, God.

23:21.704 --> 23:22.792
- It's out.

23:25.273 --> 23:29.799
Do you know how fast this
kind of news gets to prison?

23:29.843 --> 23:30.844
Charlie...

23:32.236 --> 23:33.586
They already know
you're coming.

23:33.629 --> 23:35.065
Do you know what
they're gonna do to you?

23:35.109 --> 23:36.589
- Please, I...

23:36.632 --> 23:38.547
- Everything that you ever
thought of doing to a child

23:38.591 --> 23:40.680
and a whole lot worse.
- Please don't...

23:40.723 --> 23:42.203
- They're gonna use
your sick mind against you

23:42.246 --> 23:44.988
unless you tell me right now
where she is.

23:45.032 --> 23:46.816
- Oh, God.
- You understand?

23:46.860 --> 23:48.644
They're gonna tear you apart.

23:48.688 --> 23:50.341
I'm the only thing
that can help you.

23:50.385 --> 23:53.040
I'm the only thing standing
between you and gen pop.

23:53.083 --> 23:57.914
So think real hard right now
and tell me, where is she?

24:01.091 --> 24:03.616
- I, um...

24:03.659 --> 24:05.792
I, uh, I--
[knock at door]

24:05.835 --> 24:07.358
- Come on, Charlie.

24:07.402 --> 24:09.839
Come on, just tell me, man.

24:09.883 --> 24:12.102
It's okay, tell me.

24:12.146 --> 24:14.061
[knock at door]
- I don't know.

24:14.104 --> 24:15.279
I don't know.

24:16.890 --> 24:17.891
I don't know.

24:18.935 --> 24:20.328
I don't know.

24:20.371 --> 24:21.764
- Sit tight.

24:26.334 --> 24:27.944
What the hell? What's going on?

24:27.988 --> 24:29.859
I almost had him in there.
What are you doing?

24:31.339 --> 24:33.080
- We got footage off
the tip-line.

24:33.123 --> 24:35.082
Something you need to see.

24:35.125 --> 24:37.954
- Wait, Kev, is it Charlie?
- No, it's not.

24:39.782 --> 24:41.392
- What the hell's going on?

24:41.436 --> 24:43.743
- A woman said she saw a girl
matching Brianna's description

24:43.786 --> 24:46.397
with a white male at
a gas station at 2:37 p.m.

24:46.441 --> 24:48.008
He was grabbing the key
to the bathroom.

24:48.051 --> 24:49.357
- It wasn't Charlie?

24:49.400 --> 24:50.924
- No, height and weight
are all wrong.

24:50.967 --> 24:52.273
- Okay, Adam, this is 2:46.

24:52.316 --> 24:54.841
This is well after
the witness saw them inside.

24:54.884 --> 25:01.891
♪

25:13.424 --> 25:15.122
That's it.

25:15.165 --> 25:17.385
And it's not enough
for a facial rec.

25:21.911 --> 25:22.956
- Hold on.
- What?

25:22.999 --> 25:24.479
- That's a white Honda.
- Okay.

25:24.523 --> 25:26.437
- He said white car, Charlie.
He mentioned a white car

25:26.481 --> 25:28.352
when he was trying
to give me other suspects.

25:31.007 --> 25:32.661
Son of a bitch.

25:32.705 --> 25:39.712
♪

25:44.064 --> 25:45.892
You said you saw a white car?

25:47.371 --> 25:49.373
Yeah.

25:49.417 --> 25:50.418
White car.

25:54.117 --> 25:55.684
Did you see the plates?

25:56.903 --> 25:58.339
Did you see the driver?

26:00.210 --> 26:01.734
Try.

26:01.777 --> 26:03.170
Come on, man.

26:10.743 --> 26:13.180
- I will never tell you
a thing.

26:13.223 --> 26:17.880
♪

26:22.537 --> 26:22.668
.

26:22.711 --> 26:27.020
- Okay, so it's a white
2003, 2005 Honda sedan.

26:27.063 --> 26:28.978
That's the only specs we were
able to get from the video.

26:29.022 --> 26:30.850
And the witness is talking
with a sketch artist now.

26:30.893 --> 26:32.765
- Okay, so we pull
every white Honda

26:32.808 --> 26:34.636
in Chicago that matches
those stats.

26:34.680 --> 26:36.029
- All right, I got

26:36.072 --> 26:38.118
eight registered sex offenders
in that area.

26:38.161 --> 26:39.772
- All right, track them.
Get alibis.

26:39.815 --> 26:40.947
We got body details?

26:40.990 --> 26:43.602
- 5'10" to 6 feet,
180 to 200 pounds.

26:43.645 --> 26:44.690
- Put them in front
of the parents.

26:44.733 --> 26:46.953
- Yup.

26:46.996 --> 26:48.476
- Charlie is not talking.

26:48.519 --> 26:50.043
He ain't ever going
to talk to me now.

26:50.086 --> 26:52.523
- Well, he's a witness,
one of our only.

26:52.567 --> 26:53.829
- Boss, I messed up.
I pushed him too hard.

26:53.873 --> 26:55.048
It's not gonna work.

26:55.091 --> 26:56.745
- You got
to make it work, Adam.

27:00.531 --> 27:01.837
- All right.

27:04.666 --> 27:07.974
[suspenseful music]

27:08.017 --> 27:09.845
- Oh, my God.

27:16.547 --> 27:18.027
- Son of a bitch.

27:23.729 --> 27:25.078
All right, wait here.

27:29.822 --> 27:31.693
You cleared the house?
- Yeah.

27:31.737 --> 27:33.042
No one but him.

27:33.086 --> 27:34.609
We'll book him.
Loop you all in.

27:34.653 --> 27:35.828
- All right.

27:35.871 --> 27:42.835
♪

27:42.878 --> 27:44.967
- You son of a bitch.
I'm gonna kill you!

27:45.011 --> 27:46.142
- Don't make it worse.
- Where's my daughter?

27:46.186 --> 27:47.753
- Don't make it worse.

28:36.236 --> 28:38.717
- Get out of my house.
- I can't.

28:38.760 --> 28:40.544
Not until you talk to me.

28:40.588 --> 28:42.024
- Get the hell out of my house.
- What did you see?

28:42.068 --> 28:44.766
Just tell me what you saw.
Did you see the driver?

28:44.810 --> 28:47.464
Did you see a plate?
- [scoffs]

28:47.508 --> 28:48.901
- You keep telling me
you'd never hurt a child.

28:48.944 --> 28:51.773
This one might be dying.
- Because of you.

29:00.956 --> 29:03.611
- You asked me if I have a kid.

29:03.654 --> 29:05.613
I do.

29:05.656 --> 29:07.789
She's a girl.
She's seven just like Brianna.

29:07.833 --> 29:10.618
So you can imagine
what I thought when I saw you.

29:12.054 --> 29:14.796
It's a little overwhelming
being a dad sometimes,

29:14.840 --> 29:17.233
being scared, being protective.

29:17.277 --> 29:19.801
You know, loving your kid
so much that it hurts.

29:21.934 --> 29:24.284
Charlie, it made me
get it wrong.

29:24.327 --> 29:27.026
I didn't believe you when you
said you'd never hurt a child.

29:29.158 --> 29:31.944
- I love children.
- I know.

29:31.987 --> 29:33.641
I understand that now.

29:37.340 --> 29:39.212
This little girl
could be dying.

29:39.255 --> 29:40.691
She could be dead.

29:42.998 --> 29:45.174
She's a real kid
out there, Charlie.

29:46.828 --> 29:49.831
I can't lose her because I was
too scared to see you right.

29:53.966 --> 29:54.967
- [sighs]

29:57.186 --> 29:59.580
I didn't see the driver.

30:01.887 --> 30:02.844
- Okay.

30:05.281 --> 30:07.675
And the car?

30:07.718 --> 30:08.894
- It was a Honda.

30:10.330 --> 30:12.114
I didn't see the plate.

30:12.158 --> 30:13.202
- Okay.

30:13.246 --> 30:16.902
- Um, there was a decal,
though,

30:16.945 --> 30:20.557
like a--like a sticker.

30:20.601 --> 30:23.212
Indiana Hoosiers.

30:23.256 --> 30:26.172
On the top left.

30:26.215 --> 30:27.695
And that's all.

30:30.219 --> 30:33.005
That's it? No thank you?

30:40.186 --> 30:42.057
- I pity you, Charlie.

30:42.101 --> 30:45.582
On some level, I do.

30:47.062 --> 30:49.195
But I meant everything
I said to you in that box.

30:52.241 --> 30:53.982
You are a predator,

30:54.026 --> 30:56.071
and if you ever
touch a child again,

30:56.115 --> 30:58.726
I'm gonna find ya,

30:58.769 --> 31:02.208
and I will rain down every bit
of hell that I promised.

31:02.251 --> 31:09.258
♪

31:15.221 --> 31:16.570
White Honda has

31:16.613 --> 31:18.615
an Indiana University decal
in the back window.

31:18.659 --> 31:20.226
- Okay, so we go wide.

31:20.269 --> 31:23.011
Run against anyone that pops
with a white Honda in Chicago.

31:23.055 --> 31:25.884
- Well, the Honda doesn't match
any of our eight sex offenders,

31:25.927 --> 31:27.233
and none of them
tie back to the college.

31:27.276 --> 31:28.625
- No matches in POD footage.

31:28.669 --> 31:30.932
- I got a 2003 white Honda

31:30.976 --> 31:32.629
registered to
a Priscilla DeFranco.

31:32.673 --> 31:35.067
She graduated from
Indiana University

31:35.110 --> 31:36.938
30 years ago.
She lives in Ravenswood.

31:36.982 --> 31:38.940
- DeFranco?
Don't we have a DeFranco?

31:38.984 --> 31:40.072
- Joseph DeFranco.

31:40.115 --> 31:42.291
Adam, you and I,
we interviewed him.

31:42.335 --> 31:44.076
He lives three doors down
from the Halls.

31:44.119 --> 31:45.468
He's the one who said that

31:45.512 --> 31:47.427
Niles gets so upset
when Brianna's in the yard.

31:47.470 --> 31:52.258
- Okay, what do we have on him?
- Uh, one sec.

31:52.301 --> 31:54.913
He's 39,

31:54.956 --> 31:57.393
single, works in tech,
got laid off two months ago.

31:59.134 --> 32:00.962
- He had a kid who died.

32:01.006 --> 32:02.964
Six years ago, his daughter
died in a car crash.

32:03.008 --> 32:05.140
He got divorced a year later.

32:05.184 --> 32:06.794
Height and weight,
it seems like a match.

32:06.837 --> 32:07.969
- Sarge, it's him.
- Okay.

32:08.013 --> 32:09.840
Drop an anchor
at Joseph DeFranco's.

32:09.884 --> 32:11.668
We're heading to you.
- Copy.

32:11.712 --> 32:14.671
[tense music]

32:14.715 --> 32:21.722
♪

32:23.028 --> 32:24.899
- Chicago PD!

32:27.206 --> 32:28.337
- Going down.

32:31.775 --> 32:33.081
- Clear.

32:33.125 --> 32:35.127
- Clear. Going upstairs.

32:39.522 --> 32:42.351
- Hailey, he's coming to you.
Go!

32:42.395 --> 32:44.136
- Yeah, I got eyes.

32:44.179 --> 32:51.186
♪

32:59.412 --> 33:01.762
- I got the car.

33:01.805 --> 33:03.982
- I got you.
- [groans]

33:04.025 --> 33:05.113
- Don't move.

33:06.375 --> 33:08.725
Stay down!
Hands behind your back.

33:10.379 --> 33:12.294
- Anything?

33:12.338 --> 33:13.861
- She's not here.

33:13.904 --> 33:20.085
♪

33:23.610 --> 33:23.784
.

33:23.827 --> 33:26.047
- Hey, you understand that?

33:26.091 --> 33:28.919
Joseph, we have you.

33:28.963 --> 33:30.443
Joseph.

33:32.097 --> 33:33.750
We found Brianna's DNA

33:33.794 --> 33:36.014
in your mother's car,
on your jacket.

33:39.539 --> 33:41.019
So where is she?

33:45.632 --> 33:47.808
Joseph.

33:47.851 --> 33:49.375
This can be
a lot harder for you

33:49.418 --> 33:51.333
if you don't talk to us.

33:51.377 --> 33:53.640
A lot harder.

33:53.683 --> 33:54.989
Come on, look at me.

33:56.947 --> 33:58.036
- A man....

34:01.387 --> 34:03.824
A man who has a daughter.

34:03.867 --> 34:07.045
- Go ahead,
a man who has a daughter.

34:07.088 --> 34:08.959
A man who has a daughter, what?

34:13.616 --> 34:15.618
You took her
'cause you lost your daughter

34:15.662 --> 34:17.490
and you wanted
to be a father again?

34:21.885 --> 34:25.672
- Joseph, do you know that we
have your mother in here too?

34:25.715 --> 34:26.803
You used her car,

34:26.847 --> 34:28.370
so she could be
on the hook for this

34:28.414 --> 34:30.503
if you don't talk to us.

34:30.546 --> 34:32.592
You don't want that for her.

34:32.635 --> 34:34.550
Where did you take her?

34:38.163 --> 34:40.469
- He is near catatonic.

34:40.513 --> 34:42.428
All right, where else are we?

34:42.471 --> 34:43.777
- His cell phone's been off

34:43.820 --> 34:45.866
since 7 a.m. the day
that Brianna disappeared.

34:45.909 --> 34:47.476
- CPIC has his car,

34:47.520 --> 34:48.477
and they're running
traffic cams,

34:48.521 --> 34:49.783
taking out his GPS,

34:49.826 --> 34:51.654
and his mama claimed
she doesn't know anything.

34:51.698 --> 34:53.003
- Huh.
- All right, what about tech?

34:53.047 --> 34:54.527
- Nothing on his laptop.

34:54.570 --> 34:56.703
Hasn't used his credit card
in two days, but get this.

34:56.746 --> 34:59.097
He's been pulling out
500 in cash every week.

34:59.140 --> 35:00.533
- Got something from his house.

35:00.576 --> 35:02.012
Search recovered a receipt

35:02.056 --> 35:03.536
dated a month ago
to a children's store.

35:03.579 --> 35:05.494
He bought a kid's bed,
a kid's comforter,

35:05.538 --> 35:07.148
stuffed animals.
- He built her a room.

35:07.192 --> 35:08.845
- Yeah, he was gonna hold her.

35:08.889 --> 35:10.673
Guy's still grieving,
wants a kid,

35:10.717 --> 35:14.155
takes Brianna,
but panics when she resists.

35:14.199 --> 35:15.765
- So if he bought furniture,

35:15.809 --> 35:17.158
he had to transport it
somewhere.

35:17.202 --> 35:18.464
There's gotta be
footprints, right?

35:18.507 --> 35:19.987
- Mm-hmm, but the guy
wouldn't rent a truck.

35:20.030 --> 35:21.510
- No, he'd move it himself.

35:21.554 --> 35:23.425
What are the chances he didn't
turn his cell phone off

35:23.469 --> 35:24.992
when he did?
- I'm on it.

35:25.035 --> 35:27.995
[tense music]

35:28.038 --> 35:35.045
♪

35:36.917 --> 35:39.920
- We're two minutes out.
- Copy, we're going in now.

35:39.963 --> 35:42.923
Brianna!
- Brianna, we're the police.

35:45.012 --> 35:47.493
- Brianna, we're Chicago police
here to help.

35:47.536 --> 35:48.929
Come on, kid. Come on.

35:48.972 --> 35:50.844
- Brianna?

35:55.196 --> 35:56.980
Brianna, honey,
it's the police.

35:57.024 --> 35:59.722
You're okay. Can you call out?

35:59.766 --> 36:01.115
Brianna.
- Son of a bitch.

36:01.159 --> 36:02.638
Come on.

36:06.773 --> 36:09.558
Kim.
- You got her?

36:09.602 --> 36:13.519
Tell me you have her.
- Yeah, I got her.

36:13.562 --> 36:15.434
She got a pulse.

36:15.477 --> 36:16.870
- Come on, baby.

36:16.913 --> 36:18.785
- Come on.
Let's get you out of here.

36:21.091 --> 36:23.006
- 5021 Eddie, we're coming out
with her now,

36:23.050 --> 36:25.444
north east corner.
Get me those paramedics.

36:30.753 --> 36:33.626
- Hey.
- Oh, there you are.

36:34.888 --> 36:36.672
Um, did you hear back from Med?

36:36.716 --> 36:38.152
- Mm.

36:38.196 --> 36:40.633
Yeah, she's out of surgery.
She did real well.

36:40.676 --> 36:42.896
She had a brain bleed,
but they stopped it.

36:42.939 --> 36:45.507
- That's good.
We brought her home safe.

36:45.551 --> 36:46.900
- Yeah.

36:50.947 --> 36:54.516
- I killed you, didn't I,
with what I said about Makayla?

37:02.916 --> 37:05.484
Let me be clear, okay?

37:05.527 --> 37:08.138
I know that you love her
and she loves you, Adam.

37:08.182 --> 37:09.357
- Okay then why--

37:09.401 --> 37:10.663
- I'm not going
to take it away from you.

37:10.706 --> 37:12.534
- Then why you got me
in a standby position?

37:12.578 --> 37:14.144
- I'm not.
I'm trying to protect her,

37:14.188 --> 37:16.669
that's all.
- But I'm not leaving.

37:20.020 --> 37:21.717
I know she's not mine.

37:24.677 --> 37:26.722
But she is.

37:26.766 --> 37:29.986
She feels like my kid.
I love her like she's my kid.

37:30.030 --> 37:31.510
And I just...

37:32.815 --> 37:34.513
Do not want to feel like
I'm gonna lose her.

37:34.556 --> 37:36.166
I can't do that all the time,
you know?

37:36.210 --> 37:38.647
- You won't.

37:38.691 --> 37:39.996
- I understand things
are complicated

37:40.040 --> 37:41.563
between you and me, I do.

37:41.607 --> 37:44.740
I just need to know that
I have a place with her too.

37:44.784 --> 37:47.308
I got a right to be
in her life going forward.

37:47.352 --> 37:51.269
- Okay, we can do that.

37:51.312 --> 37:53.009
- Really? Yeah?

37:53.053 --> 37:54.663
- Yeah.

37:54.707 --> 37:56.665
Yeah, we were going
to do it before, right,

37:56.709 --> 37:59.929
with our baby.
This modern family.

38:01.714 --> 38:03.237
Let's do that now with Makayla.

38:05.239 --> 38:07.197
- Well, I would
like that very much.

38:07.241 --> 38:10.200
[soft pensive music]

38:10.244 --> 38:12.768
- Okay.

38:12.812 --> 38:14.204
- Come here.

38:18.905 --> 38:20.254
- And that's what they said.

38:20.298 --> 38:23.213
It's like they're all
moving so fast

38:23.257 --> 38:25.172
you can't see them.
- Hmm.

38:25.215 --> 38:27.653
- Just kind of
moving around up there.

38:27.696 --> 38:28.871
- Yeah, just moving?

38:28.915 --> 38:31.047
Just dancing around
up there like this?

38:31.091 --> 38:32.571
- [chuckles]

38:32.614 --> 38:34.834
- I think we might have
to revisit that one in class.

38:34.877 --> 38:36.270
What?
You can't sleep with those.

38:36.314 --> 38:37.619
What are you, crazy?

38:37.663 --> 38:40.622
Get marker all over
your sheets.

38:40.666 --> 38:43.625
Hey, can I talk to you
about something?

38:43.669 --> 38:45.105
- Okay.

38:45.148 --> 38:47.716
- So Kim and I were thinking,
if it's okay with you,

38:47.760 --> 38:49.327
of course,
that maybe the three of us,

38:49.370 --> 38:51.764
we could live together
kind of permanent like.

38:51.807 --> 38:53.374
- You're gonna live
on the couch?

38:53.418 --> 38:54.854
- [chuckles]
No.

38:54.897 --> 38:57.378
There's a three bedroom
apartment just upstairs,

38:57.422 --> 39:00.599
so we would move in there,
then I could have my own room.

39:00.642 --> 39:02.775
And you and I, we could hang
out together all of the time.

39:02.818 --> 39:04.646
I could pick you up from
school, that sort of thing.

39:04.690 --> 39:05.995
What do you think?
That sound okay?

39:06.039 --> 39:08.084
- Yeah.
- Yeah?

39:08.128 --> 39:09.912
- Do you think
my new friend, Teddy,

39:09.956 --> 39:11.784
can come over to the new place?

39:11.827 --> 39:13.655
- Your new friend from school?

39:13.699 --> 39:15.265
He's pretty generous
with his stickers,

39:15.309 --> 39:17.920
so I guess we could
probably work something out.

39:17.964 --> 39:20.096
All right, lights out, kid.

39:20.140 --> 39:23.273
- He gave me another one today.
- Yeah?

39:23.317 --> 39:25.754
- He keeps a bunch of them
in his car.

39:25.798 --> 39:29.105
- Oh, his car.
You mean his parent's car?

39:29.149 --> 39:31.064
- No, it's his car.

39:31.107 --> 39:33.675
He has one all himself.

39:33.719 --> 39:36.417
- Mack, is Teddy a teacher
from school?

39:36.461 --> 39:40.160
- No, he's the man who
waits by the fence for me.

39:40.203 --> 39:42.423
Only ever wants to talk to me.

39:42.467 --> 39:45.426
[tense music]

39:45.470 --> 39:46.601
♪

39:46.645 --> 39:48.211
- I assure you
if anyone saw anything--

39:48.255 --> 39:49.735
- I want to see the footage.

39:51.737 --> 39:53.303
- We always have
at least three TAs--

39:53.347 --> 39:54.783
- Scroll to yesterday.

39:54.827 --> 40:01.834
♪

40:04.358 --> 40:05.751
- Oh, my God.

40:08.014 --> 40:10.451
- This is officer Adam Ruzek,
badge number 59054.

40:10.495 --> 40:11.844
- Can you fast forward?
- Mm-hmm.

40:11.887 --> 40:13.019
- Do it now.

40:13.062 --> 40:14.150
- I need patrol backup
to 1240 Walnut.

40:15.500 --> 40:17.719
Yeah, I need
to do a grid search.

40:17.763 --> 40:24.770
♪

40:31.516 --> 40:32.778
Okay.

40:35.215 --> 40:38.348
- Okay, okay.
I know you're panicked.

40:38.392 --> 40:40.220
I need you to have a seat.
- We're not having a seat.

40:40.263 --> 40:41.221
What the hell
is going on, Alanah?

40:41.264 --> 40:42.309
I ran his plates.

40:42.352 --> 40:44.050
- I know this--
- They're related.

40:46.095 --> 40:48.446
- Yes.

40:48.489 --> 40:50.491
His name's Theo Morris.

40:50.535 --> 40:52.928
He's Makayla's uncle
on her paternal side.

40:52.972 --> 40:54.364
- Oh, Jesus.

40:54.408 --> 40:56.192
- It hasn't reached
my desk yet,

40:56.236 --> 41:00.066
but he's filed a petition
for full custody.

41:02.547 --> 41:04.113
- Adam.

41:04.157 --> 41:11.164
♪

41:18.824 --> 41:21.783
[suspenseful music]

41:21.827 --> 41:28.834
♪

41:48.897 --> 41:51.900
[wolf howls]
